text: "A 50-year-old male presents with complaints of leg swelling and pain in the heel, which started a few days after he began an antibiotic course for a lower respiratory tract infection. Examination reveals signs suggestive of Achilles tendinitis. Which of the following best describes the mechanism of action of the drug most likely responsible for his condition?",
