subcategory: "10-pyqs",
tags: ["PYQ", "NEET PG 2023"],
text: "A 3-year-old child presents with fever and a maculopapular rash that started on the face and spread downward. Examination reveals Koplik spots on the buccal mucosa.\nThe causative organism responsible for this illness belongs to which of the following categories?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "DNA virus", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "Enveloped, negative-sense single-stranded RNA virus", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "C", "text": "Non-enveloped, positive-sense RNA virus", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Double-stranded RNA virus", "is_correct": false}],
